#: ../../user_interface/menu/view_menu/rgb_parade.rst:19
msgid ""
"Displays a histogram of R, G and B components of the video data.  This data "
"is a 3D histogram."
msgstr ""
"Visualizza un istogramma delle componenti R, G e B dei dati video. Questi "
"dati sono un istogramma 3D."

#: ../../user_interface/menu/view_menu/rgb_parade.rst:21
msgid ""
"The horizontal axis represents the horizontal axis in the video frame. The "
"vertical axis is the pixel luminance from 0 to 255. The brightness of the "
"point on the graph represents the count of the number of pixels with this "
"luminance in this column of pixels in the video frame."
msgstr ""
"L'asse orizzontale rappresenta l'asse orizzontale nel fotogramma video, "
"mentre quello verticale è la luminosità dei pixel da 0 a 255. La luminosità "
"del punto sul grafico rappresenta il conteggio del numero di pixel con "
"questa luminosità in questa colonna di pixel nel fotogramma video."

#: ../../user_interface/menu/view_menu/rgb_parade.rst:23
msgid ""
"In the sample screenshot below of a green screen with a shadow on it and "
"with a right edge that reveals a white wall, you can see how the scope "
"works. The circled regions labeled 1 are on the right side representing the "
"fact that there are several columns of pixels that are quite bright whitish/"
"gray. So these regions are higher up on the Y axis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/view_menu/rgb_parade.rst:25
msgid ""
"The regions labeled 2 are in the middle of the scope and the dip in the "
"graph there shows the shadow on the screen at this point. The average "
"luminance of the pixels in these columns is lower."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/view_menu/rgb_parade.rst:33
msgid ""
"For more information, see :ref:`Granjow's blog <waveform_and_RGB_parade>` on "
"the waveform and RGB Parade scopes. This blog gives some information on how "
"to use the data provided by the RGB Parade to do color correction on video "
"footage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/view_menu/rgb_parade.rst:35
msgid ""
"The RGB Parade option in the View menu is somewhat different from the  :ref:"
"`rgb_parade_MLT` in that :menuselection:`View --> RGB Parade` displays the "
"histogram in the application whereas the **RGB Parade** effect writes the "
"histogram into the video output file."
msgstr ""

